==English==
===Noun===
'''octopi'''

# a plural form of [[octopus]].

===Etymology===
* The ''-i'' plural comes from the belief that [[octopus]] is a [[Wiktionary Appendix:Latin second declension|Latin second declension]] noun. In fact, it belongs to the [[Wiktionary Appendix:Latin third declension|Latin third declension]]. The usual plural is [[octopuses]], and [[octopodes]] is the latin plural, and [[octopi]] which are also correct.